candidates.title: Add feature flag for dictionaries
candidates.body: Add feature flag for dictionaries. The following commands do not include the built-in dictionary. ```shell script % cargo build ``` If you have not built binaries with built-in dictionaries, you will need to prepare the dictionaries. For more information on preparing dictionaries, see the following link: - Lindera IPADIC Builder - Lindera UniDic Builder - Lindera ko-dic Builder - Lindera CC-CEDICT Builder The "ipadic" feature flag allows Lindera to include IPADIC. ```shell script % cargo build --features=ipadic ``` The "unidic" feature flag allows Lindera to include UniDic. ```shell script % cargo build --features=unidic ``` The "ko-dic" feature flag allows Lindera to include ko-dic. ```shell script % cargo build --features=ko-dic ``` The "cc-cedict" feature flag allows Lindera to include CC-CEDICT. ```shell script % cargo build --features=cc-cedict ``` If you want all dictionaries built-in, build as follows. ```shell script % cargo build --features=full ```

candidates.title: Do not perform strict checks on left context id and right context id in unk.def
candidates.body:
Do not perform strict checks on left context id and right context id in `unk.def`.
If the right context ID in `unk.def` is different from the left context ID, output a warning message.
ko-dic is different from IPADIC.

Here is ko-dic's unk.def:
```
DEFAULT,1801,3566,3640,SY,*,*,*,*,*,*,*
SPACE,1798,3563,996,SP,*,*,*,*,*,*,*
ALPHA,1796,3532,824,SL,*,*,*,*,*,*,*
CYRILLIC,1796,3532,824,SL,*,*,*,*,*,*,*
GREEK,1796,3532,824,SL,*,*,*,*,*,*,*
HANGUL,1803,3569,10055,UNKNOWN,*,*,*,*,*,*,*
HANJA,1795,3561,-803,SH,*,*,*,*,*,*,*
HIRAGANA,1796,3532,824,SL,*,*,*,*,*,*,*
KANJI,1796,3532,824,SL,*,*,*,*,*,*,*
HANJANUMERIC,1795,3561,-803,SH,*,*,*,*,*,*,*
KATAKANA,1796,3532,824,SL,*,*,*,*,*,*,*
NUMERIC,1797,3562,3563,SN,*,*,*,*,*,*,*
SYMBOL,1801,3566,3640,SY,*,*,*,*,*,*,*

```

```
% lindera-ipadic-builder -h

A Japanese morphological dictionary builder for IPADIC.

USAGE:
    lindera-ipadic-builder [OPTIONS]

FLAGS:
    -h, --help       Prints help information.
    -v, --version    Prints version information.

OPTIONS:
    -s, --dict-src <DICT_SRC>                The dictionary source path.
    -d, --dict-dest <DICT_DEST>              The dictionary destination path.

    -D, --user-dict-dest <USER_DICT_DEST>    The user dictionary destination path.
```

candidates.title: Make the binary smaller by compressing the dictionary
candidates.body:
I made the binary smaller by compressing the dictionary. (Instead, the decompression runtime is taken first).
I implemented this feature in my [lindera-js](https://github.com/higumachan/lindera-js) with the aim of making the executable file smaller.

If you guys are interested in this feature, I'd like to include it in this repository by using the features flag to toggle it on and off.

achivement:

```bash
cargo build --release
ls -lah target/release/
```

the execute file `target/release/lindera` size is `72M` to `11M`.
but the `bench-constructor` result is slower than no compress.

```
bench-constructor       time:   [28.210 ms 28.319 ms 28.431 ms] 
```

```
bench-constructor       time:   [590.35 ms 591.92 ms 593.58 ms]                              
```

candidates.title: implement binary data reading and writing for user dictionary
candidates.body:
# Pull Request

## Problem

The more lines in `userdic.csv`, the longer it will take to create the `tokenizer`.

In my environment, with 180,000 rows of CSV, it takes about 14 seconds to run `lindera/examples/userdic_example.rs`.

## Solution

Create a binary version of the user dictionary in advance.
How about loading it in the `tokenizer`?

With the same CSV data of 180,000 rows It takes about 7 seconds to run `lindera/examples/userdic_example.rs` using the binary loading method.

The code is a proposed implementation.
Please let us know what you think of this approach.

candidates.title: Support user dictionary.
candidates.body:
Closes #37 

This adds a feature to load user dictionaries from (UTF-8 encoded) CSV files. Compiling an user dictionary to binary representation runs on the fly. It currently works only with the default ipadic system dictionary.

For usage example, please see the [example code](https://github.com/mocobeta/lindera/blob/feat/support-user-dictionary/lindera/examples/userdic_example.rs).
